flavor.name: CS.LANG
flavor.operationalization: The language is compliant to RFC 3066 (Tags for the Identification of Languages ). The format for the language to describe is ss [-CC] where ss stands for the language tag, according to ISO 639-1 and CC for the optional country code, ISO-3166 alpha-2. The resulting language indicator is not case sensitive.

dataType.name: GLIST
dataType.represents: complex date datetime decimal duration ordinal quantity count

attribute.name: period
attribute.desc: If non-NULL, specifies that the sequence alternates, i.e., after this many increments, the sequence item values roll over to start from the initial sequence item value. For example, the sequence (1; 2; 3; 1; 2; 3; 1; 2; 3; ...) has period 3; also the sequence (1; 1; 2; 2; 3; 3; 1; 1; 2; 2; 3; 3; ...) has period 3 too.

attribute.name: denominator
attribute.desc: The integer by which the index for the sequence is divided, effectively the number of times the sequence generates the same sequence item value before incrementing to the next sequence item value. For example, to generate the sequence (1; 1; 1; 2; 2; 2; 3; 3; 3; ...) the denominator is 3.

element.name: head
element.desc: This is the start-value of the generated list.

element.name: increment
element.desc: The difference between one value and its previous different value. For example, to generate the sequence (1; 4; 7; 10; 13; ...) the increment is 3; likewise to generate the sequence (1; 1; 4; 4; 7; 7; 10; 10; 13; 13; ...) the increment is also 3.
